com.facebook.buck.core.parser.buildtargetpattern

Class UnconfiguredBuildTargetParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.core.parser.buildtargetpattern.UnconfiguredBuildTargetParser

  • public class UnconfiguredBuildTargetParser
extends Object
    Factory that parses a string into UnconfiguredBuildTarget.

    Fully qualified build target name looks like `cell//path/to:target#flavor1,flavor2`, where `cell` and `path/to` components is allowed to be empty, and flavors may not be specified along with `#` sign. So a minimum valid build target string is `//:target` indicating a target named `target` at the package on the root path of the default cell without flavors

    • Method Detail

      • parse

        public static UnconfiguredBuildTarget parse(String target)
                                     throws BuildTargetParseException
        Parse a string representing fully qualified build target, validating build target format

        Fully qualified build target format is `cell//path/to:target#flavor1,flavor2` where cell may be an empty string, and flavors may be omitted along with `#` sign

        The target must be in canonical form. Importantly, the cell name must be the canonical name.

        Parameters:
        target - String representing fully-qualified build target, for example "//foo/bar:bar"
        Throws:
        BuildTargetParseException - If build target format is invalid; at this moment BuildTargetParseException is unchecked exception but we still want to declare it with the hope to make it checked one day; this type of exception would be properly handled as user error

      • parse

        public static UnconfiguredBuildTarget parse(String target,
                                            boolean intern)
                                     throws BuildTargetParseException
        Parse a string representing fully qualified build target, validating build target format

        Fully qualified build target format is `cell//path/to:target#flavor1,flavor2` where cell may be an empty string, and flavors may be omitted along with `#` sign

        The target must be in canonical form. Importantly, the cell name must be the canonical name.

        Parameters:
        target - String representing fully-qualified build target, for example "//foo/bar:bar"
        intern - Whether to intern parsed instance; once interned the instance stays in memory forever but subsequent hash map/set operations are faster because Object.equals(Object) is cheap
        Throws:
        BuildTargetParseException - If build target format is invalid; at this moment BuildTargetParseException is unchecked exception but we still want to declare it with the hope to make it checked one day; this type of exception would be properly handled as user error
